<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-08-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-08-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 180/64.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Chile</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Third Assistant Secretary of
                                State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">S. S.
                                        Kaiser Wilhelm der Grosse</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Via
                                        wireless and Halifax</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-08-10"><hi rend="italic">August
                                        10, 1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Repeat to you, Gen. Carter, Capt. Hulse, Mr. Dawson, best thanks for your
                            attention and kindness.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Pedro Montt.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>